ZH: 走廊里的灯光很昏暗。
EN: The lights in the corridor are dim.

ZH: 他迷失在漫长的走廊中。
EN: He got lost in the long corridor.

ZH: 这座建筑物拥有一个宽敞的走廊。
EN: The building has a spacious corridor.

ZH: 每当我走过走廊，我都能闻到新鲜的油漆味。
EN: Every time I walk through the corridor, I can smell the fresh paint.

ZH: 走廊里传来嘈杂的声音。
EN: There were noisy voices coming from the corridor.

ZH: 我们必须保持走廊的整洁。
EN: We need to keep the corridor clean.

ZH: 走廊尽头有一扇钢制的门。
EN: There is a steel door at the end of the corridor.

ZH: 走廊的地板很滑。
EN: The floor of the corridor is slippery.

ZH: 走廊的墙上挂着一幅画。
EN: There is a painting hanging on the wall of the corridor.

ZH: 我总是不小心撞到走廊的墙上。
EN: I always accidentally bump into the walls of the corridor.

ZH: 走廊通向教室。
EN: The corridor leads to the classrooms.

ZH: 我经常在走廊上碰到我的朋友们。
EN: I often run into my friends in the corridor.

ZH: 他们搬到了一个没有尽头的走廊里。
EN: They moved into a corridor that seems to have no end.

ZH: 走廊里没有任何装饰。
EN: There is no decoration in the corridor.

ZH: 学生们排成队伍走过走廊。
EN: The students walk in a line through the corridor.

ZH: 走廊弯曲起伏，布满了花纹的地砖。
EN: The corridor twists and turns, with patterned floor tiles.

ZH: 老师嘱咐学生们保持安静在走廊里行走。
EN: The teacher instructed the students to walk quietly in the corridor.

ZH: 我们仰望着高高的走廊天花板。
EN: We look up at the high ceiling of the corridor.

ZH: 走廊里有一排从天花板到地面的玻璃窗。
EN: There is a row of floor-to-ceiling windows in the corridor.

ZH: 走廊的尽头有一个紧急出口。
EN: There is an emergency exit at the end of the corridor.
